First note the symmetry about \(x=3\).  Let \(u=x-3\).  Then when \(x=2\), \(u=-1\); when \(x=4\), \(u=1\), and
\[
\int_{2}^{4}(x-3)^{3}\,dx
=\int_{u=-1}^{1}u^{3}\,du
=\Bigl[\tfrac{u^{4}}{4}\Bigr]_{-1}^{1}
=\frac{1^{4}}{4}-\frac{(-1)^{4}}{4}
=\frac{1}{4}-\frac{1}{4}
=0.
\]
So the net signed area is 0.
